title: @OspreyVB Travels to Savannah State for Tuesday Night Match
text: @OspreyVB Just A Second: Tuesday night is just the second time UNF and Savannah State have met in program history. The first match occurred on Sept. 13, 1991, which was UNF's second match in the entire program's history. UNF won that match 3-0. Tuesday Night Fun: UNF is 2-0 in Tuesday night matches this season, picking up wins against Florida A&M on Sept. 15 and Bethune-Cookman last Tuesday. Savannah State is the third MEAC team for the Ospreys on a Tuesday night. Scouting Savannah State: Seeks first win of the season... all matches played this season have only gone to three sets... 0-1 against Atlantic Sun teams already this season, falling 3-0 to Kennesaw State on Aug. 29... Gabrielle Nathaniel (79), Caitlynn Masoe (79), Makayla Tam (78) and Christian Lyle (75) all have over 70 kills for the season... Alexis Washington averages 3.21 digs per set.
